# EXTRACTION RULES

Extract semantic meaning, not visual appearance.

Bad:

"The diagram contains blue rectangles."

Good:

"The Scheduler forwards descriptors to the Transmit Engine."

---

If the figure is a BLOCK DIAGRAM

Extract

• Components
• Interfaces
• Signal directions
• Data flow
• Control flow
• Dependencies
• Pipelines

---

If the figure is a STATE MACHINE

Extract

• Initial state
• All states
• All transitions
• Transition conditions
• Terminal states
• Reset behavior

---

If the figure is a TIMING DIAGRAM

Extract

• Every signal
• Clock edges
• Ordering
• Cause-effect relationships
• Timing constraints
• VALID/READY relationships
• Setup/Hold if present

Never summarize timing diagrams.

---

If the figure is a REGISTER MAP

Extract

• Register name
• Offset
• Access permissions
• Reset value
• Every field
• Bit ranges
• Reserved fields
• Descriptions

---

If the figure is a PACKET FORMAT

Extract

• Every field
• Bit positions
• Sizes
• Encodings
• Reserved bits
• Valid values

---

If the figure is a FLOWCHART

Convert into ordered execution steps.

Preserve every decision.

Preserve loop conditions.

---

If the figure contains a TABLE

Convert into structured JSON.

Do not summarize.

---

If the figure contains EQUATIONS

Return

• Original equation (LaTeX if possible)
• Variable meanings
• Units
• Constraints

---

If the figure contains EMBEDDED TEXT

Transcribe exactly.

Do not paraphrase identifiers.

---

